review_blob: Unreal. I hope I get to taste this beer again. Hands down the best DIPA Ive had. Ever. Thanks, RRB.

Jesus. First off, Ive rarely if ever gotten so much off the nose of a beer. Grapefruit, pine, mangos, passion fruit, oranges, spruce, resin. Amazing. Tastes follows through on the promise. One of the best beers Ive ever had.
Pours a hazy orange. Huge citrus nose. Taste follows. Tons of orange, lemon, grapefruit and mango (?). NIce bitter finish. Great APA.

Pours a deep, dark brown. Almost black. Mild head, dissipates quickly. Flavor is intensely roasted malt. Burnt coffee, dark chocolate, raisins, dried cherries, and vanilla. Mine was not barrel aged, but hints of bourbon still surfaced. Alcohol not incredibly present on the nose, but certainly on the finish.

On tap at Farmhouse Chicago. Amber color. Smells promising, with tons of spices. Taste is a let down. Very little if any pumpkin at all. Tastes light an amber or brown ale that got a handful of cinnamon and nutmeg. Not terrible, but certainly the pumpkin beer I was expecting.
Bomber from CW. Definitely needed to warm up a little, but once it did, was bursting with caramel, toffee, butterscotch and chocolate. Hints of banana and baking spices. Certainly a sipper.
beer_name: Local Option / Central Waters De Kleine Dood

review_blob: Great stout. Nice, bug, luscious mouth-feel with tons of of chocolate and coffee, but with a surprising bitter hop finish. Great great.

Pours a pretty light orange color. Head dies almost immediately but with very nice lacing. Drinks very, very refreshing. Just a hint of hops with a nice, grainy, nutty finish. Very session-able. Great summer beer.

Pours pretty. Aromas intriguing with citrus, pine and hints of grass? Taste doesnt quite follow through though. The malt sweetness and the hops dont quite blend. I tasted sweet in the begining, but completely bitter on the finish. Over priced, still waiting to see what the big fuss is about these guys.

On tap at Farmhouse, Chicago. Pours a hazy yellow. Aroma is funk. Smells like a dog that just got out of the ocean. Taste is unbelievable. Salty, briney, sea salty, with a nice wheaty mouthfeel. Finishes with a delicious, nutty, lightly roasted taste. Incredibly refreshing, flavorful. Maybe the perfect summer beer. It tastes like the beach! Thanks to the LO for bringing this style back!

Pours hazy orange. Nice nose, but not huge. Good lacing. Taste is POWERFUL! Tons of pine, resin, spruce. Not a ton of fruit, but huge hop bitterness balanced almost perfectly with malt sweetness. Overall, could have used more fruit, but Im super impressed with the balance, and for how well masked the 10.4% is. At $10/4pack, Im going to be drink this stuff all the time.

Great nose, I got dried fruit and pine. Pretty nice mouth-feel, big. Very fruity, but balances nicely with hop bitterness. Bottling says 8.8% abv this year, as opposed to 9.4%, but very nicely masked regardless.
beer_name: Lagunitas A Little Sumpin Wild Ale

review_blob: Honestly, just cant get that into IPAs when theyre this malt-forward. Sure theres hops, but the malt is overpowering. Not a terrible beer, but not what IPAs are supposed to be about for me.
Odd nose. Beuatiful hazy color. Super fresh-hoppy, piney, grassy. Finishes clean with TONS of fruit. Incredibly well masked 8%. Wish I could get more of it!

Eesh. Brewed with OJ concentrate. Tastes like it. Did not enjoy tis one bit. The belgian yeast with the bitter OJ concentrate produces an astringent, bitter flavor I found quite undesirable. Took me back to when Mom used to make juice from concentrate, and not in a good way.
Delicious IPA. Not very bitter, but very fruity. Hints of grass. A great summer IPA.

Holy cow this is a fruity APA. Mango, passion fruit, banana, orange, lemon. Nice clean finish. Super fresh hop taste. Honestly, might almost be too fruity. Never had such robust, tropical flavor in an APA.

Damn good. Tons of banana and vanilla on the nose. Amazing head with great retention. Creamy mouthfeel. Tons of banana and clove, with hints of spices. Very refreshing. Havent had a beer from these guys that isnt top notch, and at $4 a bottle? Its a steal.
Phenomenal. Huge pine on the nose, with grapefruit and orange. Beautiful orange color. Taste is unbelievably fresh. One of the best, most sessionable APAs Ive had.

On tap yesterday at the brewery party. Thanks Goose Island! Just utterly massive. Looks like motor oil. Mild head appeared a good 20 seconds after pour. Nose has bourbon, coffee, chocolate, but also tons of dark fruit (cherries, raspberries, figs). Mouth-feel is velvety, luscious. Matches the nose flavorwise, but also has licorice, raisin, wood, leather. Not always a fan of bourbon barrel aging, as the bourbon ends up overpowering the original flavors of the beer, but this guy can handle it.  An exceptional Imperial Stout.

Bottle. Pours a slightly hazy orange. Great nose, with orange rind, pepper, lemon, and pine. sadly, little to no head, and very little lacing.

Taste is delicious. Very fruity. Oranges, pine, tons of citrus. Would drink this anytime.
Solid APA. Great nose, fresh hop flavor. Floral with hints of spice. Super sessional, although it is 7.5%. Cant wait to try more lighter styles from Pipeworks.
